UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Orlando Ismael MUNIZ, Defendant-Appellant. No. 13-12352

Non-Argument Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. Feb. 24, 2014. Peggy Morris Ronca, Myrna Amelia Mesa, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Orlando, FL, Robert E. O’Neill, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Tampa, FL, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Joseph Robert Johnson, Law Offices of Joseph R. Johnson, PA, Ocoee, FL, for Defendant-Appellant. Orlando Ismael Muniz, Coleman, FL, pro se. Before MARCUS, MARTIN and FAY, Circuit Judges. *843PER CURIAM:

Joseph R. Johnson, appointed counsel for Orlando Muniz, has filed a motion to withdraw on appeal, supported by a brief prepared pursuant to Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Our independent review of the entire record reveals that counsel’s assessment of the relative merit of the appeal is correct. Because independent examination of the entire record reveals no arguable issues of merit, counsel’s motion to withdraw is GRANTED, and Muniz’s conviction and sentence are AFFIRMED.
